Jonathan Woodgate on his &ldquo;famous&rdquo; debut for Real Madrid: &ldquo;What was yours like? I&rsquo;m lucky enough to have a Real Madrid debut. Not many people are. It&rsquo;s one of those things. I&rsquo;m not bothered if people remember me for that.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Jonathan Woodgate: &ldquo;The biggest regret is I didn&rsquo;t get to play as many games as I could because of injuries. It beats me up today because I knew I could&rsquo;ve made a difference when I was there.  But Im waiting for someone else to do that on their debut to take that mantle from me!&rdquo;

Van De Beek: &ldquo;Yes, Real Madrid are interested in me, but you are going very fast.&rdquo; [Cope]<br />
<br />
Van de Beek: &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t want to talk about what&rsquo;s there or what is not, now I want to be focused on the match against Vitesse.&rdquo;

Gareth Bale has been left out of the Real Madrid squad for tomorrow&rsquo;s friendly v Red Bull Salzburg. Currently no sign of him being reintegrated into the 1st team picture nor the relationship with Zinedine Zidane being rebuilt or moving clubs before Spain&rsquo;s transfer deadline #RMFC<br />
